characters.name: Moana

additional_info.title: FAQ
additional_info.body:
If Moana – Of Motunui quests, can I choose which princesses I ready? If I had Princesses already readied or I ready them with other effects later in the turn, can they quest that turn?

A: If you choose to use Moana’s We Can Fix It ability to ready your other Princess characters, you must ready all of them. If you quest with Moana – Of Motunui, no other Princesses can quest for the rest of your turn, regardless of whether you chose to ready them with her ability or they are readied later in the turn.

characters.subtitle: Of Motunui
characters.rules_text: WE CAN FIX IT Whenever this character quests, you may ready your other Princess characters. They can't quest for the rest of this turn.
characters.flavor_text: I am Moana of Motunui. You will board my boat, sail across the sea, and restore the heart of Te Fiti.

characters.name: Mr. Smee
characters.author: Kamil Murzyn / Eri Welli
characters.subtitle: Loyal First Mate
characters.flavor_text: Mr. Smee is a kind, gentle soul who lives to bring comfort and aid to a twisted old villain. Now, what good is kindness like that? —Peter Pan

characters.author: Philipp Kruse
characters.subtitle: Dragonslayer
characters.rules_text: HEROISM When this character challenges and is banished, you may banish the challenged character.
characters.flavor_text: The road to true love may be barred by still many more dangers, which you alone will have to face. —Flora

characters.name: Pumbaa
characters.author: Jenna Gray
characters.subtitle: Friendly Warthog
characters.flavor_text: You gotta put your behind in your past.

characters.name: Rapunzel

characters.rules_text: Singer 4 (This character counts as cost 4 to sing songs.)
characters.flavor_text: I should be writing symphonies, not tagging along after some headstrong teenager.

characters.subtitle: Protective Cub
characters.rules_text: Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)
characters.flavor_text: Courage comes in all sizes.

characters.flavor_text: Lilo: David! I got a new dog! David: Auwe!... You sure it’s a dog? Lilo: Uh-huh. He used to be a collie before he got ran over.

characters.name: Stitch
characters.author: Simangaliso Sibaya

additional_info.title: FAQ 1
additional_info.body:
Q: If I have multiple copies of Stitch – Rock Star in play, can I use his ability Adoring Fans multiple times on the same character?

A: The ability Adoring Fans requires you to exert the newly played character in order to draw a card. Multiple instances of this ability won’t allow you to draw extra cards, because you won’t be able to exert the same character multiple times.

additional_info.title: FAQ 2
additional_info.body:
Q: Say I have Stitch – Rock Star in play and a cost 3 character in my hand. If I use Lantern so I can pay 1 {I} less to play that character, can I then exert them to draw a card?

A: It’s not the cost of the character you play that’s reduced by Lantern; it’s the amount you have to pay. The new character’s cost would still be 3, so they wouldn’t qualify to be a fan of Stitch.

characters.subtitle: Rock Star
characters.rules_text: Shift 4 (You may pay 4 to play this on top of one of your characters named Stitch.) ADORING FANS Whenever you play a character with cost 2 or less, you may exert them to draw a card.
characters.flavor_text: The best part about a beachside concert is that there’s always room for one more.

characters.name: Timon
characters.author: Juan Diego Leon
characters.subtitle: Grub Rustler
characters.rules_text: TASTES LIKE CHICKEN When you play this character, you may remove up to 1 damage from chosen character.
characters.flavor_text: There’s all manner of tasty treats in the world—ya just gotta know where to look.

characters.name: Anna
characters.author: Valerio Buonfantino

additional_info.title: FAQ - Other
additional_info.body:
Q: Say I have an Elsa in play and I choose a ready character for Anna – Heir to Arendelle’s ability Loving Heart. If that chosen character is exerted later in the turn, will they stay exerted during the start of the next turn?

A: Yes, the chosen character will stay exerted by Anna’s effect.

characters.subtitle: Heir to Arendelle
characters.rules_text: LOVING HEART When you play this character, if you have a character named Elsa in play, choose an opposing character. The chosen character doesn't ready at the start of their next turn.
characters.flavor_text: Two sisters, one mind.

characters.name: Archimedes
characters.author: Kendall Hale
characters.subtitle: Highly Educated Owl
characters.flavor_text: Flying is not merely some crude, mechanical process. It is a delicate art. Purely aesthetic. Poetry of motion. And the best way to learn it is to do it!

characters.name: Dr. Facilier
characters.author: Isaiah Mesq

additional_info.title: FAQ - Timing
additional_info.body:
Q. When more than one effect happens at the same time, what order do they resolve in?

A. If multiple effects of yours happen at the same time during your turn, you choose the order in which they occur, then resolve the effects in that order. After that, each other player resolves their effects in turn, starting with the player to your left.

Example: If you have Dr. Facilier – Agent Provocateur in play and your Gramma Tala – Storyteller is challenged and banished, you choose whether to return the Gramma Tala card to your hand or put it into your inkwell.

additional_info.title: FAQ
additional_info.body:
Q. If I control Dr. Facilier – Agent Provocateur and one of my Floodborn characters who used their Shift ability to be played on top of another card is banished in a challenge, do all cards in the stack go back to my hand?

A. No. Because the stack of cards all go to your discard pile first and become separate cards, you could only return the top card of the stack to your hand.

characters.subtitle: Agent Provocateur
characters.rules_text: Shift 5 (You may pay 5 to play this on top of one of your characters named Dr. Facilier.) INTO THE SHADOWS Whenever one of your other characters is banished in a challenge, you may return that card to your hand.

characters.name: Dr. Facilier
characters.author: Grace Tran
characters.subtitle: Charlatan
characters.rules_text: Challenger +2 (While challenging, this character gets +2.)
characters.flavor_text: Enchantée. A tip of the hat from Dr. Facilier.

characters.name: Dr. Facilier
characters.author: Cam Kendell

additional_info.title: FAQ - Timing
additional_info.body:
Q: If I play the action Friends on the Other Side while I have Dr. Facilier – Remarkable Gentleman in play, will I draw the 2 cards from my deck before resolving his Dreams Made Real ability?

A: Dr. Facilier’s effect will not occur until after you fully resolve the text on Friends on the Other Side.

characters.subtitle: Remarkable Gentleman
characters.rules_text: DREAMS MADE REAL Whenever you play a song, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck. Put one on the top of your deck and the other on the bottom.

additional_info.body:
Q: If I use Elsa – Spirit of Winter’s ability Deep Freeze to exert 2 characters, can those characters be readied with an ability or effect such as Fan the Flames on their next turn?

A: Characters exerted with the ability Deep Freeze can be readied by Fan the Flames and similar abilities.

characters.subtitle: Spirit of Winter

additional_info.body:
Q: If I have 2 copies of Mickey Mouse – Wayward Sorcerer in play, will my Magic Broom – Bucket Brigade cost 1 {I} less or 2 {I} less?

A: Your Magic Broom will cost 2 {I} less, 1 {I} for each copy of Mickey Mouse – Wayward Sorcerer.

characters.rules_text: SWEEP When you play this character, you may shuffle a card from any discard into its player's deck.
characters.flavor_text: In the immense story-forge known as the Great Illuminary, there is always work to be done.

characters.author: Grace Tran
characters.subtitle: Biding Her Time

characters.flavor_text: You dare challenge me? Fool, my magic is more powerful than you could possibly imagine!

characters.name: Marshmallow
characters.author: Kendall Hale /Kendall Hale Anh Dang

additional_info.title: FAQ - Challenges
additional_info.body:
Q: Are abilities on characters that occur when they’re banished in a challenge considered to happen during the challenge?

A: Abilities on characters that occur when they are banished in a challenge happen during that challenge.

Example: Marshmallow – Persistent Guardian has an ability that reads, “When this character is banished in a challenge, you may return this card to your hand,” and Cheshire Cat – Not All There has an ability that reads, “When this character is challenged and banished, banish the challenging character.”
If a player challenges and banishes Cheshire Cat with Marshmallow, the Cheshire Cat’s ability would banish Marshmallow during the challenge, allowing the challenging player to return Marshmallow to their hand.

characters.subtitle: Persistent Guardian
characters.rules_text: DURABLE When this character is banished in a challenge, you may return this card to your hand.
characters.flavor_text: Hey! We were just talking about you! All good things, all good things. —Olaf

additional_info.title: FAQ - Costs
additional_info.body:
Q: If I have 2 copies of Mickey Mouse – Wayward Sorcerer in play, will my Magic Broom – Bucket Brigade cost 1 {I} less or 2 {I} less?

A: Your Magic Broom will cost 2 {I} less, 1 {I} for each copy of Mickey Mouse – Wayward Sorcerer.

characters.name: Olaf
characters.author: Giulia Riva

characters.flavor_text: The past can hurt. But the way I see it, you can either run from it or learn from it.

characters.name: Sven
characters.author: Jared Nickerl
characters.subtitle: Official Ice Deliverer
characters.flavor_text: Reindeer comin’ through! —Kristoff

characters.name: The Queen
characters.author: Matthew Robert Davies

additional_info.title: FAQ - Costs
additional_info.body:
Q: If I use Freeze and choose to exert my opponent’s The Queen – Wicked and Vain, will The Queen’s exert ability I Summon Thee allow me to draw a card?

A: No. When an ability has a cost, the card’s player must pay that cost in order to use the ability. If another effect exerts The Queen, you don’t get to draw the card from I Summon Thee. Additionally, you won’t be able to use that ability until The Queen is readied.

characters.subtitle: Wicked and Vain
characters.rules_text: I SUMMON THEE Draw a card.
characters.flavor_text: Sublime beauty matched with peerless cunning. Is there any question who is fairest?

characters.name: The Wardrobe
characters.author: Giulia Riva
characters.subtitle: Belle’s Confidant
characters.flavor_text: When you simply must have the hautest couture.

characters.name: Tinker Bell
characters.author: Adrianne Gumaya

additional_info.title: Keywords - Challenger
additional_info.body:
Challenger is additive, meaning you add up all numerical instances of it for a combined
+N {S} gain.

Example: If you have two of Tinker Bell – Peter Pan’s Ally in play, each of them gives your Peter Pan characters Challenger +1, giving him a total of Challenger +2.

characters.subtitle: Peter Pan’s Ally
characters.rules_text: Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.) LOYAL AND DEVOTED Your characters named Peter Pan gain Challenger +1. (They get +1 while challenging.)

characters.name: Ursula
characters.author: Simangaliso Sibaya
characters.subtitle: Power Hungry
characters.rules_text: IT'S TOO EASY! When you play this character, each opponent loses 1 lore. You may draw a card for each 1 lore lost this way.
characters.flavor_text: The first Rule of Villainy: If you’re going to be evil, you’ve got to have STYLE.

characters.name: Yzma

characters.flavor_text: When I want your opinion, I will give it to you!

characters.name: Zeus

characters.subtitle: God of Lightning
characters.rules_text: Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.) Challenger +4 (While challenging, this character gets +4.)
characters.flavor_text: A little lightning solves a whole lot of problems.

characters.subtitle: Prince Ali

characters.flavor_text: I’ll take on all of you if I have to!

characters.flavor_text: You may have noticed that I'm not all there myself.

characters.name: Cruella De Vil
characters.author: Nicholas Kole
characters.subtitle: Miserable as Usual
characters.rules_text: YOU'LL BE SORRY! When this character is challenged and banished, you may return chosen character to their player's hand.
characters.flavor_text: When she stops by, misery is company.

characters.name: Duke of Weselton
characters.author: R. La Barbera / L. Giammichele
characters.subtitle: Opportunistic Official
characters.flavor_text: Sorcery! I knew there was something dubious going on here.

characters.name: Flynn Rider
characters.author: Leonardo Giammichele
characters.subtitle: Charming Rogue
characters.rules_text: HERE COMES THE SMOLDER Whenever this character is challenged, the challenging player chooses and discards a card.
characters.flavor_text: I didn’t want to have to do this, but you leave me no choice.. . .

characters.name: Genie
characters.author: Giulia Riva
characters.subtitle: On the Job
characters.rules_text: Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.) DISAPPEAR When you play this character, you may return chosen character to their player's hand.
characters.flavor_text: Can your friends go ‘Abracadabra, let ’er rip’ and then make the sucker disappear?

characters.rules_text: Shift 6 (You may pay 6 to play this on top of one of your characters named Genie.) Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.) PHENOMENAL COSMIC POWER! Whenever this character quests, you may play an action with cost 5 or less for free.

characters.name: Genie
characters.author: Matt Chapman
characters.subtitle: The Ever Impressive

characters.name: Hans
characters.author: Massimiliano Narciso
characters.subtitle: Scheming Prince

characters.name: Horace
characters.author: Isaiah Mesq
characters.subtitle: No-Good Scoundrel
characters.flavor_text: Well, they ain’t in here, Jasper.

characters.name: Iago
characters.author: Brian Weisz
characters.subtitle: Loud-Mouthed Parrot

characters.name: Jasper
characters.author: Jochem Van Gool
characters.subtitle: Common Crook
characters.rules_text: PUPPYNAPPING Whenever this character quests, chosen opposing character can't quest during their next turn.
characters.flavor_text: Now, look here, Horace, I warned you about thinkin’.

characters.name: John Silver
characters.author: Jared Nickerl
characters.subtitle: Alien Pirate

characters.flavor_text: Don't be too put off by this. . . hunk of hardware.

characters.name: Jumba Jookiba
characters.author: Milica Celikovic
characters.subtitle: Renegade Scientist
characters.flavor_text: Created something? Ha! But that would be irresponsible and unethical. I would never, ever. . . make more than one.

characters.name: Kuzco
characters.author: Grace Tran
characters.subtitle: Temperamental Emperor
characters.rules_text: Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.) NO TOUCHY! When this character is challenged and banished, you may banish the challenging character.
characters.flavor_text: I asked for emerald and that is clearly jade! What is wrong with you people?

characters.name: Lady Tremaine
characters.author: Leonardo Giammichele
characters.subtitle: Wicked Stepmother
characters.rules_text: DO IT AGAIN! When you play this character, you may return an action card from your discard to your hand.
characters.flavor_text: If your chores are done, then clearly you don’t have enough of them.

characters.name: Mad Hatter
characters.author: Rosa la Barbera
characters.subtitle: Gracious Host
characters.rules_text: TEA PARTY Whenever this character is challenged, you may draw a card.
characters.flavor_text: Mad Hatter: Would you like a little more tea? Alice: I haven’t had any yet, so I can’t very well take more.

characters.name: Megara
characters.author: Aubrey Archer
characters.subtitle: Pulling the Strings
characters.rules_text: WONDER BOY When you play this character, chosen character gets +2 this turn.
characters.flavor_text: A deal’s a deal. But falling in love was never supposed to be part of it.

characters.name: Mickey Mouse
characters.author: Alex Accorsi / Kendall Hale
characters.subtitle: Artful Rogue
characters.rules_text: Shift 5 (You may pay 5 to play this on top of one of your characters named Mickey Mouse.) MISDIRECTION Whenever you play an action, chosen opposing character can't quest during their next turn.
characters.flavor_text: Quiet as a... well, you know.

characters.name: Mickey Mouse
characters.author: Juan Diego Leon
characters.subtitle: Steamboat Pilot
characters.flavor_text: On rivers throughout the Inklands, the little steamboat's whistle answers the cheery tunes of its pilot.

characters.name: Mother Gothel
characters.author: Javier Salas
characters.subtitle: Selfish Manipulator
characters.rules_text: SKIP THE DRAMA, STAY WITH MAMA While this character is exerted, opposing characters can't quest.
characters.flavor_text: Great. Now I’m the bad guy.

characters.name: Peter Pan
characters.author: Koni
characters.subtitle: Never Landing
characters.rules_text: Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
characters.flavor_text: What’s the matter, Hook? Can’t you fly?

characters.name: Tamatoa
characters.author: Jeff Murchie

additional_info.title: FAQ 1
additional_info.body:
Q: If I have multiple copies of Belle – Strange but Special in play, can I apply the effect of her Read a Book ability multiple times in a turn?

A: Each copy of Belle can apply her ability once per turn.

Example: If you have 2 copies of Belle – Strange but Special in play, you may put 2 extra cards into your inkwell each turn.

additional_info.title: FAQ 2
additional_info.body:
Q: When I use Belle – Strange but Special’s Read a Book ability, can I place any card into my inkwell or does it need to have the inkwell icon?

A: Belle’s Read A Book ability only allows you to put another card into your inkwell; it doesn’t override any other rules of the normal process of adding a card to your inkwell. The card must have the inkwell icon and you must show it to all players before putting it in your inkwell.

additional_info.title: FAQ - Timing
additional_info.body:
Q. When more than one effect happens at the same time, what order do they resolve in?

A. If multiple effects of yours happen at the same time during your turn, you choose the order in which they occur, then resolve the effects in that order. After that, each other player resolves their effects in turn, starting with the player to your left.

Example: If you have Dr. Facilier – Agent Provocateur in play and your Gramma Tala – Storyteller is challenged and banished, you choose whether to return the Gramma Tala card to your hand or put it into your inkwell.

additional_info.title: FAQ - Challenges
additional_info.body:
Q: If I banish a shifted Floodborn card in a challenge while I have a card that lets me gain 1 lore when I banish a character, how much lore do I gain?

A: No matter how many cards are in a shifted character’s stack, they still count as a single character. Only the top card of a shifted character’s stack is considered banished for the purpose of effects like this.

Example: If you banish a shifted character with Simba – Rightful Heir, you still gain only 1 lore from his ability I Know What I Have to Do.

additional_info.title: FAQ
additional_info.body:
Q: Say I have Stitch – Rock Star in play and a cost 3 character in my hand. If I use Lantern so I can pay 1 {I} less to play that character, can I then exert them to draw a card?

A: It’s not the cost of the character you play that’s reduced by Lantern; it’s the amount you have to pay. The new character’s cost would still be 3, so they wouldn’t qualify to be a fan of Stitch.

Q: If I use Freeze and choose to exert my opponent’s The Queen – Wicked and Vain, will The Queen’s exert ability I Summon Thee allow me to draw a card?

A: No. When an ability has a cost, the card’s player must pay that cost in order to use the ability. If another effect exerts The Queen, you don’t get to draw the card from I Summon Thee. Additionally, you won’t be able to use that ability until The Queen is readied.

additional_info.title: FAQ - Other
additional_info.body:
Q: What happens if a card tells me to perform an action and I can’t do everything it tells me to do?

A: If a card says to perform an action, do as much as you can to fulfill the requirements. This does NOT apply to actions that are part of a cost.

Example: Develop Your Brain says “Look at the top 2 cards of your deck. Put one into your hand and the other on the bottom of the deck.” If you only have one card left in your deck, you look at that card and then put it in your hand.
